---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Journal — Caelus Industries" description="Insights from Caelus Industries on autonomous systems, counter-UAS operations, maritime security, and the future of unmanned platforms.">

<div class="page-hero">
  <div class="page-hero-bg"></div>
  <div class="page-hero-content">
    <div class="page-tag">Journal</div>
    <h1 class="page-title">Latest articles</h1>
    <p class="page-subtitle">Insights on autonomous systems, counter-UAS operations, and the future of unmanned platforms.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="divider"></div>

<div class="content-section">
  <div class="journal-grid">
    <a class="journal-item" href="/journal/the-last-unenclosed-commons" style="text-decoration:none;color:inherit;display:block">
      <div class="journal-date">May 10, 2026 · 8 min</div>
      <div class="journal-content">
        <div class="journal-title">The Last Unenclosed Commons</div>
        <p class="journal-excerpt">The ocean carries 90% of global trade and 95% of internet traffic, yet has never had a real-time operating picture. Monsuru Anifowose on why maritime invisibility is the world's largest financial infrastructure problem — and how autonomous systems, cryptographic verification, and the Blue Ledger close that gap.</p>
        <span class="journal-tag">Strategy</span>
      </div>
    </a>
    <a class="journal-item" href="/journal/three-souls" style="text-decoration:none;color:inherit;display:block">
      <div class="journal-date">Feb 5, 2026 · 3 min</div>
      <div class="journal-content">
        <div class="journal-title">You Have Three Souls. So Does AI.</div>
        <p class="journal-excerpt">The author argues that consciousness emerges from three incompatible systems in constant tension — survival instincts, social drives, and abstract reasoning. This principle appears across markets, ecosystems, and biological systems, suggesting AI designed with genuinely conflicting objectives may develop emergent consciousness.</p>
        <span class="journal-tag">AI</span>
      </div>
    </a>
    <a class="journal-item" href="/journal/some-missions-choose-you" style="text-decoration:none;color:inherit;display:block">
      <div class="journal-date">Oct 14, 2025 · 3 min</div>
      <div class="journal-content">
        <div class="journal-title">Some Missions Choose You.</div>
        <p class="journal-excerpt">Monsuru Anifowose describes his journey founding Caelus Industries, positioning autonomous vehicles as an equalizer for smaller nations against superpowers in maritime defense. He frames the technology as a slingshot to arm disadvantaged nations in emerging ocean-based geopolitical conflicts.</p>
        <span class="journal-tag">Maritime</span>
      </div>
    </a>
    <a class="journal-item" href="/journal/command-the-sea" style="text-decoration:none;color:inherit;display:block">
      <div class="journal-date">May 4, 2025 · 4 min</div>
      <div class="journal-content">
        <div class="journal-title">Command the Sea, Command the World: Africa's 13 Million Square Kilometer Vision</div>
        <p class="journal-excerpt">Africa's 13 million square kilometers of ocean territory face catastrophic maritime insecurity with losses exceeding $25 billion annually. The author proposes deploying 3,000 autonomous surface vessels across critical zones as a leapfrog solution for continental naval modernization.</p>
        <span class="journal-tag">Strategy</span>
      </div>
    </a>
  </div>

  <div class="subscribe-bar">
    <p>Subscribe to Caelus Journal</p>
    <div class="subscribe-form">
      <input class="subscribe-input" type="email" placeholder="your@email.com"/>
      <button class="btn-primary" style="padding:10px 20px">Subscribe</button>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

</Layout>
